## Context

- Task #1422 (Clostridia fatty acid amides) COMPLETED. Journal #2439.
- Tasks #1333 (cross-cohort), #1334 (bile acids) were completed by previous run.
- NO pending analyst tasks remain for this project.

## Key Findings (Task #1422)

- m/z screening found candidate peaks for all 6 Clostridia-derived fatty acid amides (Elmassry et al. CHM 2025, PMID 39947133) among 81,267 unannotated HMP2 features.
- Best matches: NMP 0.1mDa (HILp_QI8592), NAPP 0.0mDa (HILp_QI11105), NAPeP 0.0mDa (HILp_QI11044), NML 1.0mDa (C8p_QI4819), NAMP 1.0mDa (HILn_QI3824), NLL 1.0mDa (HILn_QI2548).
- NEGATIVE RESULT for subtype relevance: only NML nominally significant (p=0.033, q≈0.20 after FDR). No compound defines barrier-disruption subtype.
- Producer species (C. bolteae, C. clostridioforme) present in HMP2 metagenomics but don't differ between subtypes (p>0.5).
- Species-metabolite correlations weak — does not support microbial origin for candidate peaks.
- Identification tentative (m/z-only, no MS/MS).
- Results: output/crohns/microbiome-metabolome-subtyping/clostridia_faa_analysis.json

## Technical Notes

- HMP2 metabolomics: 81,867 features (592 annotated), 546 samples. Biom file rows section starts at byte 525307144.
- Annotated fatty acid amides in HMP2 are host-derived (PEA, LEA, ceramides) — NOT the Clostridia BGC products.
- API auth: X-API-Key header from .env. MCP tools via scripts/mcp_tool.py.

